annotation.TEXT: Okay, she's shooting a lot of Wind horizontally, and throwing Slow Down spell circles straight at me, but... this looks like it'll be a piece of cake.
Umm... This one could be particularly tricky. Well, I can open the bottom of the box to let the bunny out at least...
So, next time will be 5-5! To be continued... Yo!
Hello, and welcome back to Tobari! Now, before I head over to 5-4, let's go back into 5-3 and see what happens if I let one of those hands hit me...
...Wow... Did I just not... acknowledge that hand's existence for a moment there? I mean, I clearly jumped straight into it as if I didn't see it, so... yeah.
DOUBLE KILL!
Alright, they're all gone now.
There's the achievement for finding the secret exit of world 5. (Apparently, this castle is good for the shop's business.)
DOUBLE KILL!
Oh, and I would've needed at least Axe for what's down there anyway.
WAH! I didn't expect to be blown off the pillar like that! At least I can just grab the heart I left back here.
Hmm... I wonder who the protectors are. Well, let's find out...
Alright, it's mid-boss time! So, who's it gonna be?
Yep! Now, let's see what the rabbit down there has to say... after I get Ground Spark.
Huh, one of my leftover Ground Sparks killed something to the right.
It's a giant maid! Fortunately, I was somehow able to bounce off of her there.
Alright, I put those mages on ice. Also, my OCD wants me to go back and get that one coin the previous mage dropped... and ice this flying duder too.
Yep, this is what I saw. Now, I obviously need Axe to get anywhere up here. Let's be careful with which blocks I break...
Yep, that just happened. I imagine this would've been a much trickier fight if I didn't happen to have Thunder, and especially if I need Axe+Mini for the secret exit...
Yep, I was able to, and he dropped several coins.
Hmm... Seems the knight statue is immune to my stomps, although bouncing off of him is safe. I wonder if I can axe him from above?
So, there you go. The hand just deals normal damage. Now let's see what 5-4 has in store for me...
Aw, only 10 coins? I just had to jinx myself recently by mentioning that it had been a while since my last 10-coin hit on the goal roulette. Anyway, about that secret exit...
Alright, now I just have to clear the level. However, this level could have a secret exit, since it's right next to the secret shop on the map.
Huh, I don't remember the Lay's Wavy ghosts being way up here last time. They were further down below the first time. I guess they spawn lined up with me.
I'll make my move eventually... Hopefully, it won't be straight into the hand again.
Master combo! (7 kills.)
Ooh, I can become Invincible here! Alright, let's go on a rampage! (Also, Shoot Rock is tempting, but I'll pass on it for the time being.)
At least I didn't axe-identally lose my Axe! Okay, so which spell should I take to fill that empty slot now? Maybe Ice?
Oh, it's those pink square bunny Thwomps again.
Oh! Well, I was able to break that block. Maybe it's possible now.
Oh, that one will come alive. I could tell because it was a slightly lighter color.
Oh, no... Is this just meant to be a death trap for the curious?
Okay, over here beyond the ghosts, we have a Slow Down mage and a couple of knight statues and skewers.
WAH! That was a cheap blind jump, game.
Mulligan.
I wonder... How many Ground Sparks does it take to defeat a knight statue?
Moon count: 29
Oh! So, I CAN break a block that high from there! I wonder if that was the intended solution, or if I was meant to do something like freeze this bunny in midair...
And, the Leisure Shop has the same merchandise as always.
Okay, that works for getting that last 1-up.
Okay, I just had to check, because it potentially looked like a good place to hide a secret, maybe.
Gotta watch out for all the mages here. I should chop my way into their chambers and take them out.
Oh, there's Mini. I wonder if I'll need that to reach the secret exit? And, since this level is the first non-boss place to get Axe that I'm aware of, maybe I'll need both Axe & Mini.
Oh, haha! The Fire mage chamber is already open, which is perfect for my Ground Spark shots!
Oh, let me guess... Certain knight statues here come alive, and I can get the Axe magic from them, right?
Whoa, geez!
BGM: Super Marisa Land - Underground
Ah, 4 Ground Sparks.
Whoa, that's a lot of Lay's Wavy potato chips! (Not nearly as many as in that one Super Marisa World level, though!)
We have seen this before, I believe during the world 2 boss battle, vs. Tsubaki. I got the Axe spell from an animated knight statue she had summoned.
And, there's another one of those checkpoint signs that doesn't care for flashy announcements.
Nope, the Axe doesn't work on them. They don't even flicker when struck like the ghosts do. Anyway, let's check out this shop...
Oh, and there's Wind here too, further to the right. Maybe I'll want that instead of Mini.
Yeah, looks like it. Fortunately, pause+exit is a thing.
Well, that didn't quite go as I planned, but there's the Magical Axe spell.
Okay, that's it for the knight statues.
And, it appears that the next spell to come along is Thunder.
Hmm... I certainly could've done better than that if I didn't hesitate back there. Also, I just realized I gave up Ground Spark for Invincible without realizing it at first.
Oh, I'm curious about those pillars near the start... Maybe they're secretly breakable with the Axe?
Well, let's see if I can do the midair freeze thing.
DOUBLE KILL!
Oh, man. We have Ground Spark as well. Also, I see that the Wind is actually coming from that maid, so I can't actually get a Wind medal. Bummer.
Also, I did see something back there that was above the Thwomps, which I think I'll need to bounce off of an enemy to reach...
Wow, that's one really slow bunny. Now, uhh... Can I even get in there? Maybe if I can break one of the higher blocks, but with the Axe's slow wind-up...
Oh, and there's the secret exit! Well, there you go! You only need Axe to reach it, which allows you to still use Thunder on the mid-boss for an easy win there.
And, there's the moon! Yeah, I'm pretty sure I did some things here in an unintended way, but whatever.
Nope, still can't do anything to the Thwomps, even while Invincible.
Oh, I should've discarded Ice the other way, but whatever. Discarded medals only take a few seconds to despawn.
Bah! That didn't go as planned either. Okay, I've taken two dumb hits just like that, so I'm just gonna restart the level. I didn't get very far anyway.
Okay, I'm getting rid of Mini for now. If it turns out I'll need it for the secret exit, I'll just get it again on a revisit after getting the normal exit.
And, on top of everything else, there's a hand too. Man, this place is crowded.
Oh, whoops. I kinda wanted Ground Spark. Well, I'll just grab the next spell that comes along.
Yep, it's the usual pre-boss selection. Of course, I'll fill up on Jellied Yams as usual.
Oh, no cutscene? And, it's a dark room... I should probably grab Light. Umm... I think I'll get rid of Axe and keep Thunder.
Okay, there's the boss's life meter.
Ooh, nice bounce to the upper ledge there. I'll have to remember that for when I speedrun this game in the future.
Pfft. Complete miss. Well, whatever. I can just get into that box up there with a properly modulated jump.
Yeah, I'm completely safe on this ledge, since the Slow Down circles are harmless, and I can easily smite her from here with Thunder.
"L is real 2401."
And, no checkpoint announcement again from that sign. Anyway, I've decided to try seeing if I need only Axe for the secret exit.
And just like that, I'm back where I was. Ooh, I bet that I can break those cracked blocks with my Axe.
Oh, another shop... and a boss door!
Looks like that's as high a block as I'm able to break from where I'm standing, but can I just break the next block to the right and hop in that way?
Yep! I was able to make that jump!
Okay, let's NOT go down into that rabbit hole this time...
Whoa, hello! I saw that maid land on something down there! However, I'm gonna just get the normal exit now, so I don't risk my moon collection.
Well, there's reachable treasure, at least.
BTW, apparently, Tobari can't run over 1-tile gaps 100% of the time, so even though she sometimes can, it's best to just jump over them.
Too bad there's no Light spell here, and I don't feel like trying to hit those ghosts with several dozen attacks from other spells.
